This is an official Melius UI-only template.

This template is a creative suite dashboard inspired by a local custom-globe-component reference. Keep the dense sidebar layout, tabbed workspace, rounded app cards, file/project management surfaces, learning cards, and animated orbit globe hero as the visual baseline. Replace sample product names and copy freely when specializing the generated app.

Preserve existing data-melius-ui-id and data-melius-ui-role values unless the user explicitly asks to rename visual editor metadata.
Do not add data-melius-id, data-melius-form, data-melius-action, or data-melius-view in the template source by default.
Do not add src/melius.app-spec.json, src/melius.client.ts, or src/melius.actions.ts to the template source.
If the user asks for saving data, forms connected to storage, runtime lists, auth, payments, notifications, or other platform behavior, add the required Melius App Spec and data-melius-* bindings during the generated app editing flow, not as part of the UI-only template baseline.
Keep UI styling editable by the visual editor: use static Tailwind className strings on real HTML elements inside the template UI kit. Do not use style props, CSS-in-JS, cn/clsx/twMerge, or dynamic className construction.
Keep forms visually complete, but treat them as presentational UI until Melius bindings are added later.
